@norse_sc I understand what you're saying, but we're not talking about two of the best to ever do it. And yes, I would. Rodgers is taking coaching from Downing right now with the Jets. You can't just audible into a different play like a video game. You have to worry about personnel not only on your own offense but the opposing defense as well. Matchups are very, very important. Especially when you have a severe lack of talent that Tannehill has had around him since 2021. AJ was the only offensive weapon that showed up that night. Julio didn't do anything to get open and help. Henry looked awful that night. His best TE that year was Mycole Pruitt. That entire offense was dead before they even had the opening kickoff set up. The first two ints came off incredibly predictable play calling. The third int was desperation throw to try and save the game with a dying clock. He was awful in that game and I think it's time to try Levis out to see what we have for the future at this point. And maybe I've been a RT supporter his entire tenure here but we can't put all that on his shoulders alone. It's kinda lazy to just blame Tannehill for that loss when he was the biggest reason we were even able to earn the #1 seed that year.
